5
00:00:48,190 --> 00:00:50,540
 Because of that diary?

6
00:00:50,540 --> 00:00:52,610
Oh, my stomach!

7
00:00:53,720 --> 00:01:00,430
So, you're saying you and I are locked up in here because of that real predator!

8
00:01:21,960 --> 00:01:25,860
Now... what do I do?

9
00:01:33,570 --> 00:01:38,400
Lift that toilet slightly and try moving it.

10
00:02:16,080 --> 00:02:21,310
Do you know a movie called Shawshank Redemption?

11
00:02:29,920 --> 00:02:33,430
I'm sure you've seen it, since it's a masterpiece.

12
00:02:33,430 --> 00:02:35,590
There's a character just like me in it.

13
00:02:35,590 --> 00:02:40,050
Someone who was falsely imprisoned and tries everything to clear his name,

14
00:02:40,050 --> 00:02:43,490
but it doesn't work, so he chooses to escape.

15
00:02:54,740 --> 00:02:55,590
This toilet?

16
00:02:55,590 --> 00:02:59,320
That's right. Why my nickname became Poop Fly,

17
00:02:59,320 --> 00:03:03,370
why I smell so bad, you get it now, right?

18
00:03:03,370 --> 00:03:06,260
You dug this yourself?

19
00:03:06,260 --> 00:03:08,900
When I came in here in the beginning, I was just like you.

20
00:03:08,900 --> 00:03:12,490
I didn't do anything wrong. I was wronged,

21
00:03:12,490 --> 00:03:14,330
so I believed I could get out.

22
00:03:14,330 --> 00:03:19,330
But... "Wow, I don't think I'll be getting out."

23
00:03:19,330 --> 00:03:22,220
It took me four years to realize that.

24
00:03:22,220 --> 00:03:26,810
I was so angry and dejected that I picked any one person to fight with.

25
00:03:26,810 --> 00:03:29,380
I got beat up to the point of near death, and got dragged into the penalty room.

26
00:03:29,380 --> 00:03:33,400
I cried all night like you, but ...

27
00:03:33,400 --> 00:03:34,890
But?

28
00:03:34,890 --> 00:03:38,110
I discovered that toilet.

29
00:03:38,110 --> 00:03:42,080
It was constructed really badly, so it didn't work too well.

30
00:03:42,080 --> 00:03:44,500
It was from that moment on...

31
00:03:44,500 --> 00:03:48,600
I dug a little at a time, and whenever I got out, I'd make it look perfectly normal.

32
00:03:48,600 --> 00:03:51,570
Whenever I got a chance, I'd cause trouble and come back in.

33
00:03:54,490 --> 00:03:57,120
I couldn't have dreamed that all the physical labor I got ridiculed for doing all my life

34
00:03:57,120 --> 00:04:00,800
would help me this much.

35
00:04:03,230 --> 00:04:06,440
Hey, young friend, listen well.

36
00:04:06,440 --> 00:04:12,660
That hole follows the sewer pipe just big enough for one person.

37
00:04:12,660 --> 00:04:16,490
I think the line here is a bit...

38
00:04:16,490 --> 00:04:19,680
 The non-separable sewer pipe connects to the main drain pipe.

39
00:04:19,680 --> 00:04:22,250
 In other words, if you go down the pipe,

40
00:04:22,250 --> 00:04:24,900
 you'll get to the main drain pipe that leads to the outside.

41
00:04:24,900 --> 00:04:28,020
 So I dug with just one spoon.

42
00:04:28,020 --> 00:04:29,850
 I kept digging.

43
00:04:29,850 --> 00:04:34,150
  And I excitedly dug the soil away.

44
00:04:43,630 --> 00:04:46,110
 And it really came out.

45
00:04:46,110 --> 00:04:51,820
If you break that pipe and go in, you should be able to get to the outside.

46
00:04:51,820 --> 00:04:55,230
Of course, the process will be the most excruciating and painful, but deal with it. Freedom smells of blood...

47
00:04:55,230 --> 00:04:59,960
Freedom naturally smells of blood, no, it stinks of shit!

48
00:04:59,960 --> 00:05:01,640
- Wait a minute. 
 - Why?

49
00:05:01,640 --> 00:05:04,170
You want me to escape?

50
00:05:04,170 --> 00:05:06,290
Right!

51
00:05:06,290 --> 00:05:11,100
I'm already feeling victimized since I've been falsely accused, and you want me to be an escapee?

52
00:05:12,440 --> 00:05:15,100
Then say to yourself, "Someone will get me out."

53
00:05:15,100 --> 00:05:20,100
"Someone will clear my name," and try waiting day and night.

54
00:05:20,100 --> 00:05:22,340
People soon forget the likes of you.

55
00:05:22,340 --> 00:05:25,340
The police? Those are the people you can trust the least.

56
00:05:25,340 --> 00:05:28,740
You'll find out after rotting in here for four, five years.

57
00:05:28,740 --> 00:05:34,220
Wow, I threw away a lotto ticket that was given to me for free.

58
00:05:34,220 --> 00:05:38,030
Well... then you should go out yourself.

59
00:05:38,030 --> 00:05:39,710
Why do you ask me to escape?

60
00:05:39,710 --> 00:05:41,590
Me?

61
00:05:44,530 --> 00:05:48,350
I've gained weight now, so I can't go through that hole.

62
00:05:48,350 --> 00:05:53,930
The food's become really good here these days, so dieting is harder than escaping.

63
00:05:56,320 --> 00:05:59,310
Still, you saw that guy,

64
00:05:59,310 --> 00:06:02,560
so if you get out, wouldn't there be a better chance of finding the real culprit?

65
00:06:02,560 --> 00:06:05,510
From seeing just the back of him eight years ago?

66
00:06:05,510 --> 00:06:08,260
Finding a needle in the white sandy beach would be faster.

67
00:06:08,260 --> 00:06:10,240
You're the one who said your memory came back for a second.

68
00:06:10,240 --> 00:06:14,470
Did you see that guy's face when you picked up that diary or not?

69
00:06:14,470 --> 00:06:16,180
That's...

70
00:06:18,190 --> 00:06:26,460
I don't know. I remembered just that I wasn't the one who tried to kill the homeless man.

71
00:06:26,460 --> 00:06:28,690
The face of the culprit...

72
00:06:28,690 --> 00:06:32,410
That's good then. It's only a matter of time before your memory comes back,

73
00:06:32,410 --> 00:06:35,000
and you just have to catch that guy yourself.

74
00:06:35,000 --> 00:06:36,990
This is the only way you've got.

75
00:06:36,990 --> 00:06:42,660
Go out that way. Find the real culprit yourself, and clear your name.

76
00:07:08,860 --> 00:07:11,260
Oh, stop talking nonsense!

77
00:07:11,260 --> 00:07:15,730
I'm already having difficult feelings. What do you mean, escape?

78
00:07:15,730 --> 00:07:19,620
Hey, I'm giving away something I worked so hard to dig up for four years!

79
00:07:19,620 --> 00:07:24,430
Never mind. To me...

80
00:07:25,190 --> 00:07:28,730
I have someone who believes that I'm innocent.

81
00:07:28,730 --> 00:07:30,670
Okay then.

82
00:07:30,670 --> 00:07:34,670
Of course you do. Let's wait and see.

83
00:07:42,190 --> 00:07:46,420
 Psychopath Diary

84
00:07:49,560 --> 00:07:55,040
 Why? Just because you killed a few people you thought I'd throw you out or something?

85
00:07:55,040 --> 00:08:01,560
 Well, if you hadn't cleaned up properly after yourself, I might have done that.

86
00:08:01,560 --> 00:08:04,820
 But you took care of things perfectly.

87
