Bo Gyeong also adored him so much...

92
00:09:06,070 --> 00:09:09,590
- Taek Soo 
 - Yes?

93
00:09:10,450 --> 00:09:14,470
That is ... You see ...

94
00:09:14,470 --> 00:09:17,390
Sunbae, you must also be heartbroken.

95
00:09:17,390 --> 00:09:23,420
Get some rest. Captain Ryoo was a really brave officer.

96
00:09:23,420 --> 00:09:26,230
From such an unfortunate accident like this...

97
00:09:26,230 --> 00:09:31,220
I wish that had been the case...

98
00:09:31,220 --> 00:09:35,000
I know... What?

99
00:09:35,000 --> 00:09:40,500
I don't think Captain Ryoo's death was an accident.

100
00:09:41,680 --> 00:09:44,190
Can you help me?

101
00:09:44,880 --> 00:09:50,410
  Until now, I was being played by that bastard.

102
00:10:03,480 --> 00:10:06,810
What a good voice he has!

103
00:10:13,330 --> 00:10:16,870
To think all of that was a delusion...

104
00:10:16,870 --> 00:10:21,630
I'm so dumbfounded at my own stupidity, it makes me so angry!

105
00:10:21,630 --> 00:10:26,250
On top of that, if I didn't kill Park Mu Seok either,

106
00:10:26,250 --> 00:10:30,620
I was made a complete fool by the real culprit!

107
00:10:42,230 --> 00:10:43,600
I'm ...

108
00:10:45,040 --> 00:10:47,190
getting out of here.

109
00:10:49,030 --> 00:10:51,400
Have you decided?

110
00:10:57,270 --> 00:10:59,010
Yes.

111
00:11:03,020 --> 00:11:06,350
The smell inside the penalty room is pretty bad, isn't it?

112
00:11:08,130 --> 00:11:11,320
Try not to end up back there again.

113
00:11:15,110 --> 00:11:19,010
You told the guard you want to meet an attorney?

114
00:11:21,220 --> 00:11:22,140
Yes.

115
00:11:22,140 --> 00:11:23,800
You can speak comfortably.

116
00:11:23,800 --> 00:11:27,350
Nowadays a corrections' position is also no different from a service job.

117
