We frequently listen to prisoners and speak face-to-face like this, too.

118
00:11:36,120 --> 00:11:42,050
I would like to request a retrial.

119
00:11:42,050 --> 00:11:43,260
Retrial?

120
00:11:43,260 --> 00:11:45,150
Truthfully,

121
00:11:50,700 --> 00:11:54,750
the day I lost my memory in an accident, I found the diary.

122
00:11:54,750 --> 00:11:58,210
I mistook the entries as something that I wrote.

123
00:11:58,210 --> 00:12:00,490
The real criminal knew I was all out of sorts,

124
00:12:00,490 --> 00:12:05,150
so he tried to frame me. And to frame me, he planted all the evidence as if I did it.

125
00:12:07,420 --> 00:12:11,540
Then, you were completely framed.

126
00:12:11,540 --> 00:12:15,270
And that predator serial killer is still running around out there.

127
00:12:15,270 --> 00:12:17,720
That's what I'm saying!

128
00:12:17,720 --> 00:12:21,130
That's serious. How could something like this ...

129
00:12:21,130 --> 00:12:23,390
I know.

130
00:12:24,180 --> 00:12:25,250
I'm really—

131
00:12:25,250 --> 00:12:28,940
How can there be a worse bastard in this world?

132
00:12:32,490 --> 00:12:33,350
What?

133
00:12:33,350 --> 00:12:37,080
I've met some bad people in my life,

134
00:12:37,080 --> 00:12:40,630
but none as evil a bastard as you.

135
00:12:43,380 --> 00:12:45,340
I'm being serious!

136
00:12:45,340 --> 00:12:48,900
You don't think I know you're trying to get out of here knowing Captain Ryoo is dead?

137
00:12:49,830 --> 00:12:52,240
Who died?

138
00:12:52,240 --> 00:12:55,820
See? Look at how you're lying without blinking an eye.

139
00:12:55,820 --> 00:12:59,310
The investigator in charge of your case, Captain Ryoo, as soon as you heard he died in an accident,

140
00:12:59,310 --> 00:13:02,320
you're trying to pull a stunt asking for a retrial or whatever!

141
00:13:02,320 --> 00:13:06,700
Bastards like you should never see the light day of again.

142
00:13:06,700 --> 00:13:11,450
Why? Because until the day you die, you're not even human.

143
00:13:11,450 --> 00:13:13,570
Never.

144
00:13:15,510 --> 00:13:17,550
Drag him away!

145
00:13:21,210 --> 00:13:24,210
  Just like you said, he's a really unbelievable bastard.

146
00:13:24,210 --> 00:13:27,210
That's why I felt I needed to tell you, especially.

147
00:13:27,210 --> 00:13:30,980
Our company's image has also suffered greatly due to him.

148
00:13:30,980 --> 00:13:34,720
Just because he looks innocent, if you treat punks like him humanely,

149
00:13:34,720 --> 00:13:36,710
you can suffer greatly.

150
00:13:36,710 --> 00:13:39,870
Yes, you're quite right.

151
00:13:39,870 --> 00:13:45,480
But Director, the 300 million fund matter you mentioned before ...

152
00:13:45,480 --> 00:13:46,980
The payment has already been sent.

153
00:13:46,980 --> 00:13:52,020
 It should be enough to buy a house for your daughter when she gets married.

154
00:13:52,020 --> 00:13:53,650
Thank you.

155
00:13:53,650 --> 00:13:58,860
It's nothing. I only wanted punks like Yook Dong Sik to be punished appropriately.

156
00:13:58,860 --> 00:14:02,320
So I wanted to return the favor to you who think the same way.

157
00:14:02,320 --> 00:14:04,510
Since we don't know what other tricks he might try,

158
00:14:04,510 --> 00:14:07,000
I'm also thinking of restricting his visitation and phone calls for a while.

159
00:14:07,000 --> 00:14:09,170
That's a great idea.

160
00:14:15,990 --> 00:14:18,710
Retrial?

161
00:14:18,710 --> 00:14:21,790
Will that work without Sim Bo Gyeong?

162
00:14:23,250 --> 00:14:28,130
I'm Sergeant Sim Bo Gyeong from the Naksan District.

163
00:14:28,130 --> 00:14:33,050
I'd like to meet the truck driver from Captain Ryoo's accident. He's in the back, right?

164
00:14:33,050 --> 00:14:35,950
That man already went home.

165
00:14:35,950 --> 00:14:40,300
What? It was an accident involving a death. Shouldn't he be in custody for investigation?

166
00:14:40,300 --> 00:14:43,360
He had insurance. And it wasn't a hit and run or a DUI.

167
00:14:43,360 --> 00:14:44,490
Even still—

168
00:14:44,490 --> 00:14:48,680
Their attorneys said they would settle with the bereaved family,

169
00:14:48,680 --> 00:14:50,590
so there's nothing left for us to do.

170
00:14:50,590 --> 00:14:51,850
This quickly?

171
00:14:51,850 --> 00:14:55,950
His attorneys must be good at their jobs.

172
00:15:09,090 --> 00:15:10,820
Did you meet the driver?

173
00:15:10,820 --> 00:15:15,680
He must make a pretty good living. It seems he hired a very good lawyer.

174
00:15:15,680 --> 00:15:18,130
No matter how certain they are of the circumstances of the accident,

175
00:15:18,130 --> 00:15:20,610
how could they settle it that rapidly?

176
00:15:20,610 --> 00:15:23,090
Are you saying someone instigated it?

177
00:15:23,090 --> 00:15:24,880
If we dig, we should be able to find out.

178
00:15:24,880 --> 00:15:28,440
I got his address for now. Let's go.

179
00:15:29,770 --> 00:15:32,150
Sunbae, hold on.

180
00:15:33,340 --> 00:15:36,560
I still haven't, the things that you told me,

181
00:15:36,560 --> 00:15:39,630
I still don't have a good grasp of it.

182
00:15:39,630 --> 00:15:44,960
So, Yook Dong Sik was framed, and the real predator murderer is a different person.

183
00:15:44,960 --> 00:15:46,910
Okay. I get that part.

184
00:15:46,910 --> 00:15:49,640
But what about Captain Ryoo?

185
00:15:49,640 --> 00:15:54,050
What does his accident have to do with this case?

186
00:15:56,650 --> 00:16:04,530
I think Captain Ryoo knew who the real predator murderer was.

187
00:16:04,530 --> 00:16:07,590
C-Captain Ryoo did?

188
00:16:19,730 --> 00:16:21,930
Didn't he apply for a new trial?

189
00:16:21,930 --> 00:16:26,310
Yes, he's got some nerve. He's shameless.

190
00:16:35,500 --> 00:16:40,850
It seems like the fact that you went to see the chief and blabbered about everything has already spread.

191
00:16:40,850 --> 00:16:46,210
Never mind the retrial, the atmosphere only became more menacing.

192
00:16:46,950 --> 00:16:49,650
So what? You're going to tell me to escape again?

193
00:16:49,650 --> 00:16:53,990
I'm just saying, take your time and think about it.

194
00:16:53,990 --> 00:16:56,460
For about five years?

195
00:16:56,460 --> 00:16:59,180
But I have Sergeant Sim.

196
00:16:59,180 --> 00:17:02,710
The most untrustworthy people in the world are police officers, I said.

197
00:17:02,710 --> 00:17:05,740
But she's different.

198
00:17:05,740 --> 00:17:09,020
She said she'll visit again soon.

199
00:17:10,330 --> 00:17:15,100
I was wondering where this smell was coming from. We have two pieces of crap now.

200
00:17:15,100 --> 00:17:19,400
What did you just say? What did you say?

201
00:17:20,270 --> 00:17:22,370
Were you saying that to us?

202
00:17:27,150 --> 00:17:30,680
You said you hurt your head and can't remember anything.

203
00:17:30,680 --> 00:17:34,270
We heard you said your killing people was all a delusion.

204
00:17:34,270 --> 00:17:38,170
Well, what then? Should we help you remember?

205
00:17:43,150 --> 00:17:47,120
Did you forget who I am?

206
00:17:48,100 --> 00:17:52,320
Predator or whatever, no one man is strong when it comes to a gang fight!

207
00:17:52,320 --> 00:17:54,190
Fellas!

208
00:17:55,720 --> 00:17:58,310
What are you doing?

209
00:17:58,310 --> 00:18:00,970
Hey, fellas.

210
00:18:03,120 --> 00:18:05,330
What are you doing over there?

211
00:18:06,880 --> 00:18:09,240
You got lucky today.

212
00:18:13,530 --> 00:18:17,060
If she's visiting, she better hurry.

213
00:18:17,060 --> 00:18:18,870
But she probably won't come.

214
00:18:18,870 --> 00:18:20,750
Ah, seriously.

215
00:18:27,560 --> 00:18:29,950
Anyone home?

216
00:18:32,800 --> 00:18:36,230
Are you home? This is the police.

217
00:18:36,230 --> 00:18:40,120
We have some questions regarding your recent accident.

218
00:18:40,120 --> 00:18:44,600
Hello? Sir.

219
00:18:46,460 --> 00:18:50,520
This is the police. Please step outside.

220
00:18:50,520 --> 00:18:54,430
Sir, we know you're inside.

221
00:18:54,430 --> 00:18:55,720
We can hear you.

222
00:18:55,720 --> 00:18:58,130
No one lives there.

223
00:18:58,130 --> 00:19:01,150
What? Why?

224
00:19:01,150 --> 00:19:03,250
They said they were moving overseas all of a sudden.

225
00:19:03,250 --> 00:19:05,870
Overseas? Where?

226
00:19:05,870 --> 00:19:10,910
Oh, I don't know. They were taking a lot of stuff so it didn't seem like a vacation, so I asked.

227
00:19:10,910 --> 00:19:14,290
They said they were looking into emmigrating while staying overseas several months or longer.

228
00:19:14,290 --> 00:19:17,080
Said they may never return.

229
00:19:21,170 --> 00:19:22,870
 Advanced Correction Implementing the Opening of the Future

230
00:19:22,870 --> 00:19:24,920
Really?

231
00:19:26,930 --> 00:19:29,860
Okay, I understand. Thanks.

232
00:19:32,650 --> 00:19:37,610
It is true he left the country. Like it's some flight-by-night...

233
00:19:37,610 --> 00:19:41,030
You were right. It's definitely suspicious.

234
00:19:41,030 --> 00:19:44,960
Killing people by using someone else?

235
00:19:44,960 --> 00:19:48,000
This isn't like the predator.

236
00:19:48,890 --> 00:19:55,960
No, probably since Dong Sik is imprisoned instead, is he being more careful?

237
00:19:55,960 --> 00:19:59,460
I can see very clearly what's going on.

238
00:19:59,460 --> 00:20:02,720
Wouldn't it be worth requesting a retrial?

239
00:20:04,190 --> 00:20:09,150
- Visitation request for Prisoner 9362, Yook Dong Sik. 
 - Yes.

240
00:20:12,560 --> 00:20:15,350
He's under discipline so there will be no visitation this week.

241
00:20:15,350 --> 00:20:17,560
Discipline? For what?

242
00:20:17,560 --> 00:20:21,690
I'm unable to say. Please try again next week.

243
00:20:31,950 --> 00:20:36,910
Whether she is a corporal or a sergeant, you still haven't heard from her I guess?

244
00:20:36,910 --> 00:20:39,680
I think visitation has ended for today, too.

245
00:20:39,680 --> 00:20:42,900
She'll probably come tomorrow.

246
00:20:42,900 --> 00:20:48,200
See? You can't trust anyone.

247
00:20:48,200 --> 00:20:50,480
There's only one solution.

248
00:20:50,480 --> 00:20:52,400
Prison break. Prison break, prison break, prison break.

249
00:20:52,400 --> 00:20:54,980
Stop talking about breaking out of prison!

250
00:20:54,980 --> 00:20:56,240
B-B-Be quiet.

251
00:20:56,240 --> 00:20:58,410
Then, why don't you escape?

252
